text: Kiesha Leggs (born April 26, 1990) is an American volleyball player. She was a member of the United States women's national volleyball team. She played at the 2013 European Cup. She played for the University of Pittsburgh's women's volleyball team, Tiboni Urbino, PTPS Piła, Chieri '76 Volleyball, and AS Saint-Raphaël Var Volley-Ball. == References == Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:American volleyball players
